{{pp-move-indef}}{{calendar}}
{{This date in recent years}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[1111]] &ndash; [[Henry V, Holy Roman Emperor|Henry V]] is crowned [[Holy Roman Emperor]].
*[[1204]] &ndash; [[Constantinople]] falls to the Crusaders of the [[Fourth Crusade]], temporarily ending the Byzantine Empire.
*[[1598]] &ndash; [[Henry IV of France]] issues the [[Edict of Nantes]], allowing [[freedom of religion]] to the [[Huguenot]]s. (Edict repealed in [[1685]].)
*[[1612]] &ndash; [[Miyamoto Musashi]] defeats [[Sasaki Kojirō]] at [[Ganryūjima|Funajima island]].
*[[1613]] &ndash; [[Samuel Argall]] captures Native American princess [[Pocahontas]] in [[Passapatanzy, Virginia]] to ransom her for some English prisoners held by [[Chief Powhatan|her father]]. She is brought to [[Henricus]] as hostage.
*[[1742]] &ndash; [[George Frideric Handel]]'s [[oratorio]] ''[[Messiah (Handel)|Messiah]]'' makes its world-premiere in [[Dublin]], Ireland.
*[[1777]] &ndash; [[American Revolutionary War]]: American forces are ambushed in the [[Battle of Bound Brook]], [[New Jersey]].
*[[1796]] &ndash; The first [[elephant]] ever seen in the United States arrives from India.
*[[1829]] &ndash; The [[Roman Catholic Relief Act 1829]] gives [[Roman Catholicism|Roman Catholics]] in the United Kingdom the right to vote and to sit in Parliament.
*[[1849]] &ndash; [[Hungarian Revolution of 1848|Hungary]] becomes a [[republic]].
*[[1861]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Fort Sumter]] surrenders to Confederate forces.
*[[1868]] &ndash; The [[Abyssinian War]] ends as British and Indian troops capture [[Maqdala]].
*[[1870]] &ndash; The New York City [[Metropolitan Museum of Art]] is founded.
*[[1873]] &ndash; The [[Colfax Massacre]] takes place.
*[[1902]] &ndash; [[James C. Penney]] opens his first store in [[Kemmerer, Wyoming]].
*[[1909]] &ndash; The [[Turkey|Turkish]] military [[31 March Incident|reverses]] the [[Ottoman countercoup of 1909]] to force the overthrow of Sultan [[Abdul Hamid II]].
*[[1919]] &ndash; The establishment of the [[Provisional Government of the Republic of Korea]].
*  1919 &ndash; [[Jallianwala Bagh massacre]]: British troops massacre at least 379 unarmed demonstrators in [[Amritsar]], India. At least 1200 are wounded.
*  1919 &ndash; [[Eugene V. Debs]] is imprisoned at the Atlanta Federal Penitentiary in Atlanta, Georgia, for speaking out against [[Conscription in the United States|the draft]] during [[World War I]].
*[[1941]] &ndash; A [[Soviet–Japanese Neutrality Pact|Pact of neutrality]] between the [[Soviet Union|USSR]] and Japan is signed.
*[[1943]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: The discovery of a [[mass grave]] of Polish [[prisoner of war|prisoners of war]] [[mass execution|killed]] by Soviet forces in the [[Katyn massacre|Katyń Forest Massacre]] is announced, causing a diplomatic rift between the [[Polish government in exile]] in London from the Soviet Union, which denies responsibility.
*  1943 &ndash; The [[Jefferson Memorial]] is dedicated in [[Washington, D.C.]], on the 200th anniversary of [[Thomas Jefferson]]'s birth.
*[[1944]] &ndash; [[Diplomatic relations]] between New Zealand and the Soviet Union are established.
*[[1945]] &ndash; World War II: [[Nazi Germany|German]] troops kill more than 1,000 political and military prisoners in [[Gardelegen (war crime)|Gardelegen]], Germany.
*  1945 &ndash; World War II: [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] and [[Kingdom of Bulgaria|Bulgarian]] forces [[Vienna Offensive|capture]] [[Vienna]], Austria.
*[[1948]] &ndash; The [[Hadassah medical convoy massacre]]: In an ambush, 79 Jewish doctors, nurses and medical students from [[Hadassah Hospital]] and a British soldier are massacred by Arabs in Sheikh Jarra near [[Jerusalem]].
*[[1953]] &ndash; [[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] director [[Allen Dulles]] launches the [[mind-control]] program [[MKULTRA]].
*[[1958]] &ndash; During the [[Cold War]], American [[Van Cliburn]] wins the inaugural [[International Tchaikovsky Competition]] in Moscow.
*[[1960]] &ndash; The United States launches [[Transit (satellite)|Transit 1-B]], the world's first [[satellite navigation]] system.
*[[1964]] &ndash; At the [[Academy Awards]], [[Sidney Poitier]] becomes the first [[African-American]] male to win the [[Academy Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] award for the 1963 film ''[[Lilies of the Field (1963 film)|Lilies of the Field]]''.
*[[1970]] &ndash; An [[oxygen]] tank aboard [[Apollo 13]] explodes, putting the crew in great danger and causing major damage to the spacecraft while en route to the [[Moon]].
*[[1972]] &ndash; The [[Universal Postal Union]] decides to recognize the People's Republic of China as the only legitimate Chinese representative, effectively expelling the [[Republic of China]] administering [[Taiwan]].
*  1972 &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: The [[Battle of An Lộc]] begins.
*[[1974]] &ndash; [[Western Union]] (in cooperation with [[NASA]] and [[Hughes Aircraft]]) launches the United States' first commercial [[Geosynchronous satellite|geosynchronous]] [[communications satellite]], [[Westar 1]].
*[[1975]] &ndash; [[Bus massacre]] in [[Lebanon]]: An attack by the [[Phalangist]] resistance kills 26 militia members of the P.F.L. of Palestine, marking the start of the 15-year [[Lebanese Civil War]].
*[[1976]] &ndash; The [[United States Treasury Department]] reintroduces the [[United States two-dollar bill|two-dollar bill]] as a [[Federal Reserve Note]] on [[Thomas Jefferson]]'s 233rd birthday as part of the [[United States Bicentennial]] celebration.
*[[1984]] &ndash; India moves into [[Siachen Glacier]] thus annexing more territory from the [[Line of Control]].
*[[1987]] &ndash; Portugal and the People's Republic of China sign an agreement in which [[Macau]] would be returned to China in [[1999]].
*[[1992]] &ndash; The Great [[Chicago Flood]].
*[[1997]] &ndash; [[Tiger Woods]] becomes the youngest [[golf]]er to win the [[Masters Tournament]].

